name: Rousette Balteatus
description:
--Fig.15--
  Rousette Balteatus is a creature from Tondra, an exoplanter located 193 light years from Earth, orbiting the star Timir.
Rousette is a giant from the deep, swimming in dark seas of cobalt, reaching astounding 32 meters in lenght. Despite his huge size, Rousette can also fly lightly through the stormy clouds of Tondra.
 The species may seem scary, but they're known to be one of the kindest creatures found, as they only eat seaweed and may be even be pet if approached carefully.
